Package com.deco2800.game.entities.factories

Class ObstacleFactory

java.lang.Object
com.deco2800.game.entities.factories.ObstacleFactory
public class ObstacleFactory
extends java.lang.Object
Factory to create obstacle entities.

Each obstacle entity type should have a creation method that returns a corresponding entity.

      public static Entity createBackground​(java.lang.String world, int width)
      Create and return a background entity having only BackgroundRenderComponent.
      Parameters:
      world - the world type; if the first word before an underscore is not one of 'asgard', 'alfheim', 'earth', 'jotunheimr', or 'hel', will default to 'asgard'. Can be null.
      width - width of the image (as given by the terrain coordinate system)
      Returns:
      background entity

    • createFloorNoCollider

      public static Entity createFloorNoCollider​(java.lang.String world)
      Create and return a floor entity that has no Physics or Collider component.

      The value of 'world' must be the same as the name of a world style with any content following an underscore afterwards. E.g. as of 22/9 the following values are all valid: 'asgard', 'hel_1', 'hel_fdsagdsa', 'jotunheimr', 'earth'. This is to allow variations on platform types while keeping a single floor type.

      Parameters:
      world - the world type corresponding the art style that the floor will mimic.
      Returns:
      floor entity
